         I hate when dipshits come into your camp and throw out the "No such thing as camp" crap. When that happens, i usually get about 5-6 of my good friends, and we each call out a mob (depending on how many spawns there are). Would suck for them to take 1 mob every 10-20 min, so more than likely they will move on. You just have to be patient, and watch what you say. Do Not use cuss words, dont use words like "KS" or "TRAIN" and don't threaten. </P><P>I love when they petition, cause then i rip them a new ass whole when the Gm arrives. Just use words that would piss them off, like calling them "NOOB" and use "EBAY". The thing to do is act badass and get them as pissed off as possible, and then when the GM arrives, act as calm as possible. Always mention to the GM on how you offered to share the camp, but they kept arguing with you and how they got all angry when you asked about sharing. Well of course they are gonna claim you didnt, but since you pissed them off, they arent going to say it very nicely, and will prolly "CAPITALIZE" some words.</P><P>Of course the Gm will not appoint you the camp, but why not piss the hell out of the dude before you have to share? most times when i resort to that method, the person says im a "two-faced bastard", and then leave the camp. </P><P>The key is just to be patient though, and make it as hard as possible for them to get a spawn. A group does not want to kill 1-2 mobs evern 10-20 min, so they will leave to another camp, just gotta be patient and persistant.</P><P>Graverazor Darkavenger<BR>60 Warlock<BR>Tunare<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=224524" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=224524</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
